# Boundaries Rule

- Do not introduce speculative abstractions.
- Do not perform opportunistic refactors.
- Do not edit unrelated modules in the same task unless required for compilation or contract alignment.
- Do not implement future-phase work during current-phase tasks.
- If task or sub-plan execution would expand project scope or phase scope, stop for an explicit replan or decision instead of absorbing the work into the current slice.
- If missing policy, dependency, or priority choices appear, return `needs_decision` or `replan_required` instead of inventing them locally.
- Prefer existing structures over creating parallel systems.
- Narrow ambiguous work instead of expanding design scope.
- Keep copied SOP workflow docs under `ai/doc/*`.
- Keep reusable workflow skills under `ai/skill/*`.
- Keep runtime-specific design docs under `ai/doc/runtime/*`, task-local closeout notes under `ai/doc/change-summaries/*`, and human-facing recovery state under `project/*`.

